  h5 Key Features
  hr
  .row
    .col-sm-7
      h3 Reliability
      h6 More reliable message processing.
      p Cloud environments are noisy and unreliable. Seeing timeouts? Wild swings in latency or performance? Ruby VM crashes or processes disappearing?
      p If a Sidekiq process crashes while processing a job, that job is lost.
      p If the Sidekiq client gets a networking error while pushing a job to Redis, an exception is raised and the job is not delivered.
      p Sidekiq Pro uses Redis's RPOPLPUSH command to ensure that jobs will not be lost if the process crashes or gets a KILL signal.
      p The Sidekiq Pro client can withstand transient Redis outages or timeouts. It will enqueue jobs locally upon error and attempt to deliver those jobs once connectivity is restored.

    .col-sm-5
      .spacer
      img.skq-copy-img.img-responsive(src='#{baseUrl}/img/reliability.png')
  hr
  .row
    .col-sm-7
      h3 Batches
      h6 Group jobs into a set and follow their progress.
      p Create a set of jobs which can be tracked as a group, programmatically or within the Sidekiq Web interface. You can see success and failure counts along with error information for failed jobs within the batch.
      p We use batches at 
        a(target='_new', href='http://www.theclymb.com/invite-from/mperham') The Clymb
        |  when uploading product catalogs to our database. Each product becomes a job, uploading 1000 products makes 1000 jobs, which are quickly processed by our swarm of Sidekiq workers. Once finished, the catalog team is notified of the results.

    .col-sm-5
      .spacer
      img.skq-copy-img.img-responsive(src='#{baseUrl}/img/batch.png')
  hr
  .row
    .col-sm-7
      h3 notifications
      h6 Receive notification via several different mediums when a batch completes.
      p
        strong Are you a human? 
        | Receive an email, Campfire or HipChat notification when a batch has completed processing.
      p
        strong Are you a robot?
        |  Receive a webhook or in-process callback when the batch is complete. Use Redis pub/sub to receive 
        strong real-time
        |  updates as your batch processes.
      p Your own custom notification mechanisms can easily be added with Sidekiq Pro's Batch callback API.

    .col-sm-5
